post_text: There aren't alot of organizations that get to celebrate their 50th anniversary. Blueprint Education is very appreciative to say that on June 4, 1969, we began this journey to help students who didn't succeed on the traditional school path. 50 years later, we are still innovating the journey for students! To everyone who has been an integral part of this evolution, WE THANK YOU! To all of the students and families who benefitted from our support, HERE'S TO YOU; your dedication and resiliency, your determination and resolve, and your motivation to reach your goals! Keep discovering and creating!

Hope High School Online
May 31, 2019 at 1:41 PM ·

FUN FACT FRIDAY

Today's fun fact is about baseball! Just some weird, interesting facts ya'll might not know.

1. In 1963, major league baseball pitcher Gaylord Perry remarked, "They'll put a man on the moon before I hit a home run." On July 20, 1969, an hour after Neil Armstrong set foot on the surface of the moon, Perry hit is first, and only, home run while playing for the San Francisco Giants. 👊

2. The average lifespan of a major league baseball: 7 pitches.⚾️⚾️⚾️⚾️⚾️⚾️⚾️

3. All major league baseball umpires must wear black underwear while on the job in case their pants split. 😎

4. In 1920, Babe Ruth out-homered very American League team. 💯

5. Babe Ruth wore a cabbage leaf under his cap to keep his head cool. He changed it every two innings. ☃️

6. Every year 56,000,000 people attend major league baseball games. 🙋‍♂️🙋‍♀️👫

7. A Costa Rican worker who MAKES baseballs earns about $2,750 annually. The average American PRO baseball player earns $2,377,000 per year. 😳

(2016 Owlcation.com)

post_text: We continue to grow and blossom at Blueprint! Congratulations to Krissyn Sumare Marina O'Connell and Chris Buehnerkemper! Well deserved :D
shared_text:
Hope High School Diamonds is with Marina O'Connell.
May 14, 2019 at 11:31 AM ·

Well, it’s official Hope Fam! It is with mixed emotions that we announce some new leadership changes for the upcoming school year. Our very own Mrs. Sumare will be accepting her new role as Director of Academics & Life Design. We will miss seeing her on our campus every day, but we are proud of the impact and outreach she will continue to make in her new position!

We are also thrilled to announce that our very own, Mrs. O’Connell and Mr. Buehnerkemper, will serve as our Hope High School Principal and Assistant Principal for the upcoming school year! They are such dedicated individuals, and we are so excited to have them both. Congratulations Team!! 😊

shared_text:
Colleen Fedigan-Walski is at Hope High School Diamonds.
September 28, 2017 at 2:28 PM · Phoenix, AZ ·

Didn't see this coming... Things are beyond busy and I apologize to those I still owe return calls to. Sigh...

My Dear Friend Vickie Isaac requested time to catch up and share an amazing gift she found, we finally catch up today at Hope High School. 3 hours later, many moments of prideful tears and being introduced to some of the most amazing souls, I leave inspired and my head spinning with ways to work together.

Shoot I woke up thinking it was only a regular Thursday kind of day. Feeling the need to unplug and relish in the light of the amazing work they are doing. We all work so so hard and most have no idea what goes behind the scene to makewjat we do happen. Feeling humble and full of hope! Thank you Vickie!

Do you like to help others? Do you like food? Hope High School will be holding the perfect event for you!

On Wednesday, January 22nd from 5PM-8PM, Hope High School and McDonald's will be teaming up at the McDonald's located on 91st Ave and Thomas Road in Phoenix. Hope High School staff will be serving food directly to patrons and a portion of the proceeds will be donated to HHS for school activities. Drive through does not count, so please come into the store and eat.

Come one! Come all! And, most importantly, come hungry!

Hope High School Diamonds
May 22, 2013 at 10:11 AM ·

I am the new principal at Hope High School, a public charter school in Phoenix. I started here in January and have spent the last few months planning to better our school for the 2013-2014 school year. As a former Social Studies teacher, I am saddened that our classrooms do not have the American Flag proudly displayed.

Please help us...we would like to get 7 flags for our classrooms...can you help us??
